text: Bagdadia salicicolella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Vladimir Ivanovitsch KuznetsovAlso transliterated Kuznetzov in 1960. It is found in Turkmenistan. The larvae feed on Salix species. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1960 Category:Bagdadia
title: Bagdadia salicicolella
